  <ethicsAndSummary>
    <summary>To investigate the efficacy, safety, and tolerability of linagliptin 5 milligrams once a day
      compared to placebo as as add-on therapy for 24 weeks to stable basal insulin treatment in
      elderly patients, 60 years of age and older, with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus and insufficient
      glycaemic control.Stable background therapy of metformin and/or alpha-glucosidase inhibitors
      is also allowed.

      In addition, this trial will assess if linagliptin reduces the risk of hypoglycaemia when
      added to background basal insulin therapy. The treatment duration of this trial (24 weeks)
      will enable assessment of the clinically relevant endpoint of a decrease in glycosylated
      Haemoglobin, a well-accepted measurement of chronic glycaemic control.</summary>
